<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Parlous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Parlous,</orth> a popular corruption of <emph>perilous,</emph> == alarming, mischievous: <cit><quote>a p. fear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 14</bibl></cit> (Snout's speech). <cit><quote>thou art in a p. state,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a p. boy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 35</bibl></cit>. In <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.154" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 154</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 3, 54</bibl> most M. Edd. <emph>parlous,</emph> O. Edd. <emph>perilous.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>